translation.knownType_DrySkin_text: Dry skin - skin looks and feels rough, itchy, flaky or scaly. Also known as xerosis or xeroderma.
translation.knownType_OilySkin_text: Oily skin - your face can get shiny as the day progresses. Pores may be more visible and are more likely to suffer acne breakouts.
translation.knownType_CombinedSkin_text: Combined skin - can be dry or normal in some areas, but oily in others, like the T-zone
translation.knownType_NormalSkin_text: Normal skin - regular texture, no or few imperfections and a soft appearance. Well-balanced
